{"id":"335074449_Scalable_Zero_Knowledge_with_No_Trusted_Setup","abstract":"One of the approaches to constructing zero knowledge (ZK) arguments relies on “PCP techniques” that date back to influential works from the early 1990’s [Babai et al., Arora et al. 1991-2]. These techniques require only minimal cryptographic assumptions, namely, the existence of a family of collision-resistant hash functions [Kilian, STOC 1992], and achieve two remarkable properties: (i) all messages generated by the verifier are public random coins, and (ii) total verification time is merely poly-logarithmic in the time needed to naïvely execute the computation being verified [Babai et al., STOC 1991].","authors":["Eli Ben-sasson","Iddo Bentov","Yinon Horesh","Michael Riabzev"],"meta":["August 2019","DOI:10.1007/978-3-030-26954-8_23","In book: Advances in Cryptology – CRYPTO 2019 (pp.701-732)"],"references":["309037347_On_Probabilistic_Checking_in_Perfect_Zero_Knowledge","267434626_SNARKs_for_C_Verifying_Program_Executions_Succinctly_and_in_Zero_Knowledge","262354053_On_the_concrete_efficiency_of_probabilistically-checkable_proofs","234794393_Proof_Verification_and_the_Hardness_of_Approximation_Problems","226120514_Progression-Free_Sets_and_Sublinear_Pairing-Based_Non-Interactive_Zero-Knowledge_Arguments","221591854_Checking_Computations_in_Polylogarithmic_Time","333081899_Aurora_Transparent_Succinct_Arguments_for_R1CS","326641097_vRAM_Faster_Verifiable_RAM_with_Program-Independent_Preprocessing","326641024_Doubly-Efficient_zkSNARKs_Without_Trusted_Setup","320849812_Zero_Knowledge_Protocols_from_Succinct_Constraint_Detection","320679714_Ligero_Lightweight_Sublinear_Arguments_Without_a_Trusted_Setup","318750493_Snarky_Signatures_Minimal_Signatures_of_Knowledge_from_Simulation-Extractable_SNARKs","315868736_Quasi-Linear_Size_Zero_Knowledge_from_Linear-Algebraic_PCPs","315847460_Computational_Integrity_with_a_Public_Random_String_from_Quasi-Linear_PCPs","311337198_A_blockchain_currency_that_be